article.headline: North Florida 90, Jacksonville 78
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Ryan Daugherty scored 28 points and Alain Laroche added 23 to lead the University of North Florida to a 90-78 win over cross-town rival Jacksonville University Wednesday in an Atlantic Sun Conference game. Jacksonville (1-17, 1-10) led once at 6-4 but tied the score on five occasions in the first half. North Florida (5-13, 2-9) held a 41-36 lead at halftime. Aubrey Conerly scored 30 points to lead Jacksonville which had a higher shooting percentage than North Florida in both halves and finished with a 50.8 percent mark from the floor compared to North Florida's 41.9 percent. But North Florida connected on 32-of-37 free throws compared to Jacksonville's 11-of-17. Rashad Williams scored 17 points, and Chris Timberlake scored 14 for North Florida. Antonio Cool scored 19 points, and Mario Brown scored 10 for Jacksonville.
